==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Three-parted
<hw>Three"-part`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Divided into,
or consisting of, three parts; tripartite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Three-parted leaf</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a leaf
divided into three parts down to the base, but not entirely
separate.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Threepence</ent>⟦br⟧
